\date{2025-02-21}
\title{Quasi-equivalences}
\taxon{Module}

\import{stt-macros}

\p{
Naively, an equivalence is a function with a two-sided inverse. We can encode this
directly in HoTT, but there is an issue; being an equivalence in this way is
\em{not a [property](stt-0009)} of a map, but instead it is extra structure. This is
in contrast to the (many equivalent) notions of coherent equivalence.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
module Foundations.QuasiEquivalence where

open import Foundations.Universes
open import Foundations.Functions
open import Foundations.FunctionInverses
open import Foundations.Singleton
open import Foundations.Sigma
open import Foundations.Identity
open import Foundations.Homotopy
}
% ```

\subtree[stt-001K]{
  \taxon{Definition}
  \title{Quasi-equivalence}

  \p{
  We want to reserve the word "equivalence" for the coherent kind in
  [[Foundations.CoherentEquivalence]], and so here we define the naive kind of
  equivalence to be called a \em{quasi-equivalence}.
  }


% ```agda
\agda{
quasi-inv : ∀ {𝓤 𝓥} {A : Type 𝓤} {B : Type 𝓥} → (f : A → B) → Type (𝓤 ⊔ 𝓥)
quasi-inv {A = A} {B} f
  = Σ[ g ∶ (B → A)] (retraction-witness f g × section-witness f g)

infix 20 _≊_
record _≊_ {𝓤 𝓥} (A : Type 𝓤) (B : Type 𝓥) : Type (𝓤 ⊔ 𝓥) where
  constructor mk≊
  field
    fwd : A → B
    fwd-qinv : quasi-inv fwd

  bwd : B → A
  bwd = fwd-qinv .fst

  section-fwd : section fwd
  section-fwd = bwd , fwd-qinv .snd .snd

  retraction-fwd : retraction fwd
  retraction-fwd = bwd , fwd-qinv .snd .fst

  section-bwd : section bwd
  section-bwd = fwd , retraction→section {g = bwd} (retraction-fwd .snd)

  retraction-bwd : retraction bwd
  retraction-bwd = fwd , section→retraction {g = fwd} (section-fwd .snd)
}
% ```
}

\subtree[stt-001L]{
\taxon{Remark}
\title{Quasi-equivalences form a groupoid on types}

% ```agda
\agda{
idqiso : ∀ {𝓤} {A : Type 𝓤} → A ≊ A
idqiso = mk≊ id (id , ~refl , ~refl)

comp-qinv : ∀ {𝓤 𝓥 𝓦} {A : Type 𝓤} {B : Type 𝓥} {C : Type 𝓦}
                  {f : A → B} {g : B → C}
                → quasi-inv f → quasi-inv g → quasi-inv (g ∘ f)
comp-qinv {f = f} {g} (finv , fret , fsec) (ginv , gret , gsec)
  = (finv ∘ ginv , ret , sec) where
  sec : section-witness (g ∘ f) (finv ∘ ginv)
  sec = g ◂ fsec ▸ ginv ~∙ gsec

  ret : retraction-witness (g ∘ f) (finv ∘ ginv)
  ret = finv ◂ gret ▸ f ~∙ fret

comp-qiso : ∀ {𝓤 𝓥 𝓦} {A : Type 𝓤} {B : Type 𝓥} {C : Type 𝓦}
            → A ≊ B → B ≊ C → A ≊ C
comp-qiso (mk≊ f fi) (mk≊ g gi) = mk≊ (g ∘ f) (comp-qinv fi gi)

bwd-qinv
  : ∀ {𝓤 𝓥} {A : Type 𝓤} {B : Type 𝓥} {f : A → B}
  → (q : quasi-inv f)
  → quasi-inv (q .fst)
bwd-qinv {f = f} (_ , η , ε) = f , ε , η

inv-qiso : ∀ {𝓤 𝓥} {A : Type 𝓤} {B : Type 𝓥} → A ≊ B → B ≊ A
inv-qiso (mk≊ fwd qinv) = mk≊ (qinv .fst) (bwd-qinv qinv)

infix 19 _≊⁻¹
infixr 19 _∙≊_

_∙≊_ : ∀ {𝓤 𝓥 𝓦} {A : Type 𝓤} {B : Type 𝓥} {C : Type 𝓦}
       → A ≊ B → B ≊ C → A ≊ C
_∙≊_ = comp-qiso

_≊⁻¹ : ∀ {𝓤 𝓥} {A : Type 𝓤} {B : Type 𝓥} → A ≊ B → B ≊ A
_≊⁻¹ = inv-qiso
}
% ```
}
